//Medial meniscus degeneration - Associated findings


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
And I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select 'Medial meniscus degeneration' from the Finding dropdown

When I select 'Chondropathy' checkbox
Then 'Tibial' checkbox is enabled
And 'Femoral' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Bone marrow edema, subchondral' checkbox
Then 'Tibial' checkbox is enabled
And 'Femoral' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Subchondral sclerosis' checkbox
Then 'Tibial' checkbox is enabled
And 'Femoral' checkbox is enable

When I select 'Meniscal cyst' checkbox
Then 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled

When I enter any number with in the range in 'Max. diameter' input field
Then 'Axial' radio button is enabled
And 'Coronary' radio button is enabled
And 'Sagittal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Meniscocapsular separation' checkbox
Then 'Meniscotibial ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscofemoral fascicle' checkbox is enabled
